description: Deletes the assets in package versions and sets the package versions' status to Disposed. A disposed package version cannot be restored in your repository because its assets are deleted. To view all disposed package versions in a repository, use ListPackageVersions and set the status parameter to Disposed. To view information about a disposed package version, use DescribePackageVersion.

parameters.name: domain
parameters.description: The name of the domain that contains the repository you want to dispose.

parameters.name: repository
parameters.description: The name of the repository that contains the package versions you want to dispose.

parameters.name: format
parameters.description: A format that specifies the type of package versions you want to dispose.

parameters.name: namespace
parameters.description: The namespace of the package versions to be disposed. The package component that specifies its namespace depends on its type. For example: The namespace of a Maven package version is its groupId. The namespace of an npm or Swift package version is its scope. The namespace of a generic package is its namespace. Python, NuGet, Ruby, and Cargo package versions do not contain a corresponding component, package versions of those formats do not have a namespace.

parameters.name: package
parameters.description: The name of the package with the versions you want to dispose.

parameters.name: versions
parameters.description: The versions of the package you want to dispose. (string) ---

parameters.name: versionRevisions
parameters.description: The revisions of the package versions you want to dispose. (string) --- (string) ---

nested_items.name: successfulVersions
nested_items.description: A list of the package versions that were successfully disposed.

nested_items.name: revision
nested_items.description: The revision of a package version.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of a package version.

nested_items.name: failedVersions
